race.description: Beechwood Hotel Country Boosted Maiden Plate
race.comment: IMMORTAL STORM (5) improving gelding yet to finish out of the minor money in three runs. Never gave up at latest when sitting up on the speed for a tough second over 1015m at Grafton. Can take control early and run the 1200m out. Finds a very weak contest. PURPLE KITTY (2) on the quick back-up after stretching in trip for a fading seventh over 2200m at Grafton on November 5. Huge training effort if he's to win this back to the 1200m. Keep safe. INDIAN HILLS (6) Dundeel mare who comes up from Victoria and now in the Joseph Burgess yard. Resumes with the one trial over 900m at Scone. Has a stack of gear changes and can surprise fresh. NORTHERN GLOW (8) looks the pick of the rest after finishing fifth over 1300m at Taree nine days ago. Fitter now and goes into the exotics.
